<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>RECONDITIONING ROTORS - INSPECTION - BLUING ROTORS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="1">
        <title>BLUING ROTORS</title>
        <para>A rotor that shows signs of bluing has been subjected to extremely high temperatures (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0401820">Figure 20
                <xref refid="f0401820"/>
            </hotlnk>
            ). This may be caused by continued hard stops or a brake system imbalance.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0401820" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0401820" filename="../figg04/G0401820.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 20. Rotor That Shows Bluing</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>If bluing is noticed, check the brake system for imbalance, if imbalance is found, repair brake system as
            required.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
